Title: Unified Geologic Map of the Moon, 1:5M, 2020
Author: U. S. Geological Survey
Who Can Use This Data: Public
URL: U. S. Geological Survey - Astropedia Lunar and Planetary Cartographic Catalog
Abstract: A "seamless, globally consistent, 1:5,000,000-scale geologic map derived from the six digitally renovated geologic maps". Consists of: unit contacts, geologic unit polygons, linear features, unit and feature nomenclature annotation, and shaded relief.
Metadata: Metadata is available with download, and on the website.
How to Cite This: USGS Astrogeology Science Center. Unified Geologic Map of the Moon, 1:5M, 2020 [digital resource: vector and raster]. Reston, VA.: U. S. Geological Survey, 2020.

Title: Ontario Classified Point Cloud (Lidar-derived)
Author: Ontario Ministry of Natural Resources and Forestry - Provincial Mapping Unit
Who Can Use This Data: Public
Abstract:
The Ontario Point Cloud (Lidar-Derived) consists of points containing elevation and intensity information derived from returns collected by an airborne topographic lidar sensor. It was designed to support agricultural soil map renewal for selected geographic areas in southern Ontario (Peterborough, Lake Erie, Halton, Milton, Brampton, GTA, Peel, CLOCA, LEAP, CNS) and portions of northern Ontario (Cochrane). The point cloud has been classified into Unclassified, Ground, Water, High and Low Noise categories and is structured into non-overlapping 1-km by 1-km tiles in LAZ format.

As this dataset is a compilation of lidar data from multiple acquisition projects, specifications, parameters, accuracy and sensors may vary by project. See the detailed User Guide and contractor metadata reports below for additional information.
How to Cite This: Ontario Ministry of Natural Resources and Forestry - Provincial Mapping Unit. Ontario Classified Point Cloud (Lidar-derived) [digital resource: grid]. Ontario Ministry of Natural Resources and Forestry - Provincial Mapping Unit, (insert date). Retrieved from http://geo.scholarsportal.info/#r/details/_uri@=2400901509.
